INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (1128,219,'AceRoom','aceroom@gmail.com','','14.139.196.5','2012-10-27 16:33:47','2012-10-27 20:33:47','I\'m having some problmes. I can get it to work with emacs running as root but I run into an error when I launch emacs as my user. \r\n\r\nIt shows\" \r\nAn error occurred while loading `/home/aceroom/.emacs\': even though I\'ve done what the xiki page says to do. It works perfectly on Mint (Minus the double click as you mentioned) but not on fedora.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/22.0.1229.94 Safari/537.4','',0,0),(1129,219,'AceRoom','aceroom@gmail.com','','14.139.196.5','2012-10-27 17:51:56','2012-10-27 21:51:56','Got it fixed. Seems that there were some temporary files which were created as root which couldn\'t be used by the user. Once I cleared them, it works well. At one point, even the double click started working but I can\'t seem to get it to work now.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.4 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/22.0.1229.94 Safari/537.4','',0,0),(1393,281,'chris','ccaaee@free.fr','','93.27.161.159','2013-02-20 06:06:14','2013-02-20 10:06:14','uname -a\r\nLinux lkj100 3.6.11-4-ARCH+ #1 PREEMPT Wed Jan 16 19:06:54 UTC 2013 armv6l GNU/Linux\r\n\r\n\r\nls /etc/network.d/ethernet-eth0\r\nls: cannot access /etc/network.d/ethernet-eth0: No such file or directory',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux i686; rv:18.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/18.0 SeaMonkey/2.15.2','',0,0),(1400,281,'doug','douglas.kipp.smith@gmail.com','','72.92.156.9','2013-02-20 13:47:21','2013-02-20 17:47:21','Chris -- sorry about that! \n\nI think the proper location of the file is: /etc/network.d/interfaces/ethernet-eth0\n\nAlso -- if that doesn\'t show up for the file, try a:\n\nfind /etc/. | grep -i \"eth0\"\n\nAnd see if you find it.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.17 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/24.0.1312.70 Safari/537.17','',1393,2),(1401,119,'Rhys Goodwin','rhys.goodwin@gmail.com','http://blog.rhysgoodwin.com','219.88.71.104','2013-06-09 02:52:46','2013-06-09 06:52:46','Hi Doug,\r\n\r\nI came across your comments over at Ken Shirriff\'s blog. I can\'t seem to be able to get my Arduino/IR Library to send MCE remote RC6 commands. \r\n\r\nI\'ve used the IRrecveDump. When I press the \'info\' key on the MCE remote the result is  0x800FB40F (36 bits). However if I try to RC6Send this  the PC won\'t respond.\r\n\r\nI know the rig is working in general as I\'m able to send NEC commands just fine.\r\n\r\nAny idea what I\'m doing wrong? \r\n\r\nCheers,\r\nRhys',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:21.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/21.0','',0,0);
